<h2 class="bac">Our Business:</h2>
<p class="bac">
More than 700 professionals in our award-winning Global Research organisation support our institutional sales and trading teams and their clients. Research Analysts add value to investor clients by providing insightful, objective and decisive research, designed to enable them to make informed investment decisions in three primary disciplines:  
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li><b>Global Equity Research Analysts</b> - provide fundamental analysis on nearly 3,000 companies in 50 countries</li>
	<li><b>Global Credit Research</b> - encompasses high-grade, high-yield, credit strategy, credit derivatives, mortgages and other structured finance, convertibles, municipals and indices</li>
	<li><b>Global Macro Research</b> - encompasses economics, currencies, commodities, rates, derivatives and equity investment strategies</li>
</ul>
<p class="bac">
The Quantitative Research groups provide clients with actionable investment ideas and solutions in the equity derivatives market. Research is based on quantitative analysis of the market environment, and requires a broad and deep understanding of the relevant derivative instruments and client risk/return profiles. 
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Overview:</h2>  
<p class="bac">
As an Associate within Global Research (positions are within Equity Research), you&#39;ll: 
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Build relationships, knowledge and experience that will open doors to a wide range of future options and opportunities</li>
	<li>Discover unlimited opportunities to challenge yourself and grow professionally </li>
	<li>Develop a network of internal professionals and clients</li>
	<li>Contribute to, and initiate, leading-edge, non-consensus, market-moving research products and reports on corporates, sectors and markets </li>
	<li>Make actionable and relevant investment recommendations, and respond to breaking news that may be share-price-sensitive</li>
</ul>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Qualifications:</h2>
<p class="bac">
Your outstanding academic achievement at both the undergraduate and postgraduate level will include an MBA, or other advanced degree, from a top-tier business school. Existing client and corporate relationships and knowledge would be an added advantage. We&#39;re also looking for a track record of superior performance in extracurricular and professional activities. 
</p>
<p class="bac">
As well as well-developed judgment and business sense, you&#39;ll need advanced skills in financial modeling; analysis and valuation; market analysis and forecasting; and knowledge of Bloomberg/Reuters and MS Office. Strong accounting, analytical, quantitative, communication and presentation skills are essential. 
</p>
<p class="bac">
You&#39;ll be expected to quickly climb the curve and contribute to extending our success, taking a well-rounded view on the entire sector, and the external factors that influence our sector.  
</p>

